{
  "texts": [
    "Furthermore, SAR-ADC and controlled oscillator-based ADCs (Current-Controlled-Oscillators -CCO, see Fig. 11c-and Voltage-Controlled-Oscillators -VCO, Fig.",
    "11d-) are more suitable to smaller technology node implementations 95,117.",
    "In this regard, and unlike the more commonly used VCO-based ADCs, CCO-based ADCs such as the one proposed by Khaddam-Aljameh et al. 71 (see Fig.",
    "11c) eliminate the need for additional conversion cycles and are amenable to trading off precision with latency.",
    "As such, this approach facilitates having one converter per column of the crossbar, thus minimizing the overall latency as no resource sharing will be required."
  ]
}